ggplot(df) + geom_violin(aes(x = weather, y = sales), fill = "#DDDDDD", color = "gray70", 
    alpha = 0.5) + geom_point(aes(x = weather, y = sales, color = weather)) + 
    theme_bw(base_size = 14) + scale_color_npg() + scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0, 
    20, 40, 60, 80, 100, 120), limits = c(15, 130)) + theme(legend.text = element_text(size = 12), 
    legend.title = element_text(size = 14), legend.background = element_rect(colour = "gray80"), 
    legend.position = c(0, 1), legend.justification = c(0, 1))

anova_brms <- brm(formula = sales ~ weather, family = gaussian(), data = df, 
    seed = 1, prior = c(set_prior("", class = "Intercept"), set_prior("", class = "sigma")))

Samples were drawn using sampling(NUTS). For each parameter, Eff.Sample 
is a crude measure of effective sample size, and Rhat is the potential 
scale reduction factor on split chains (at convergence, Rhat = 1).
eff <- marginal_effects(anova_brms)
plot(eff, points = F)[[1]] + theme_bw(base_size = 14) + scale_color_npg()

formula_lm <- formula(sales ~ weather)
X <- model.matrix(formula_lm, df)
stan_result <- stan(file = "sales_weather_design_matrix.stan", data = list(N = nrow(X), 
    K = ncol(X), X = X, Y = df$sales), seed = 1, chains = 4, iter = 2000, warmup = 1000, 
    thin = 1)
mcmc_extracted <- extract(stan_result, permuted = F)
mcmc_extracted %>% dimnames
$iterations
NULL

$chains
[1] "chain:1" "chain:2" "chain:3" "chain:4"

$parameters
[1] "b[1]"  "b[2]"  "b[3]"  "sigma" "lp__" 
color_scheme_set("gray")
mcmc_intervals(mcmc_extracted, pars = c("b[1]", "b[2]", "b[3]"), prob = 0.8, 
    prob_outer = 0.95)

mcmc_dens(mcmc_extracted, pars = c("b[1]", "b[2]", "b[3]"), prob = 0.8, prob_outer = 0.95)

mcmc_areas(mcmc_extracted, pars = c("b[1]", "b[2]", "b[3]"), prob = 0.6, prob_outer = 0.99)

print(stan_result, probs = c(0.025, 0.5, 0.975))
